dct_description_sm: This line data layer represents the Freight Analysis Framework 2.2, Region 5 for the Upper Midwest in 2010. The Upper Midwest includes: Indiana, Illinois, Michigan, Minnesota, Ohio, and Wisconsin. The dataset was originally published by the Federal Highway Administration and the Bureau of Transportation Statistics in 2010.["Freight Analysis Framework 2.2 Network Machine Readable Data Files" are distributed by the Federal Highway Administration Office of Freight Management and Operations, Operations Core Business Unit, Washington DC, 2007]
